<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="707" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="16.[1410,2618,1138,1957]" pageId="16" pageNumber="707">
<emphasis box="[1410,1645,1691,1720]" pageId="16" pageNumber="707">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The 
<collectingCountry box="[1723,1889,1691,1720]" name="Madagascar" pageId="16" pageNumber="707">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
Long-fingered Batis nocturnal. It uses caves as daytime roosts. Echolocation calls have downward FM signals, with maximum frequencies of 85-128 kHz, minimum frequencies of 54-57 kHz, peak frequencies of 57-3— 61-7 kHz, durations of 2-6—4-3 milliseconds, and intervals of 56-1-122-5 milliseconds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
